Execute the following commands from the current directory to install and
initialize the virtual environment
    pip install virtualenv
    virtualenv basicml
    virtualenv -p ~/anaconda3/bin/python3.5 basicml

You may need to change the first argument of the "virtualenv -p ..." command
above to your favorite python3.5 interpreter.

Activate the virtual environment by executing the following command
    source basicml/bin/activate

Install all the requirements by executing the following command
    pip install -r requirements.txt


NOTES
1. to update requirements.txt, "pip freeze > requirements.txt"
